Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless cellular networks and proposes a new scheme for video distribution using D2D communication. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video content delivery and proposes a new scheme for low latency wireless video distribution. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the achievable gain of the proposed scheme in terms of sum throughput and latency, which are related to information theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed scheme involves collaboration between multiple devices and an intermediate transceiver, which can be seen as a system. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed scheme may have security implications that could fall under this sub-category.
